                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-defend2268" type="age" value="24"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18200918-239-off1378" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-off1378" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-off1378" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18200918-239-cd1379" type="crimeDate">29th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-239-off1378 t18200918-239-cd1379"></join>, one handkerchief, value 3 s., the goods of a 
                     <persName id="t18200918-239-victim2269" type="victimName">man<interp inst="t18200918-239-victim2269" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-239-off1378 t18200918-239-victim2269"></join>
                     </persName>
                   unknown, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-239-person2270">
                  JAMES 
                  WAYLING
               <interp inst="t18200918-239-person2270" type="surname" value="WAYLING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-person2270" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-person2270" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was in <placeName id="t18200918-239-crimeloc1380">St. James's-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-239-crimeloc1380" type="placeName" value="St. James's-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-239-crimeloc1380" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-239-off1378 t18200918-239-crimeloc1380"></join>, and saw the prisoner in company with a gang of about twenty, going along by the side of the Queen's carriage. I saw him clap his right hand quickly into his bosom. I immediately seized him, and took the handkerchief out of his bosom. Furzeman collared him also, and brought him away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-239-person2271">
                  JOHN 
                  FURZEMAN
               <interp inst="t18200918-239-person2271" type="surname" value="FURZEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-person2271" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-person2271" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I saw twenty or thirty thieves with the prisoner. I saw him follow a gentleman in the crowd, pull his handkerchief out, and put it into his bosom. I lost the gentleman in the crowd, there was so many of them, that it was difficult to get the prisoner out. He said he picked it up; that was impossible, he could not pick it up in the crowd.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The handkerchief was thrown on my arm, two or three people wished to take it off - I did take it off.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200918-239-verdict1381" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18200918-239-verdict1381" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200918-239-punish1382" type="punishmentDescription">
